reviews.text: Very high quality beef, good service

My to go place for good Korean x Japanese BBQ. 
Reservations is recommended. Little on the pricey side but great quality per value. 

Their Kimchee is my favorite — best in town

Service is attentive and great. They will help you cook your meats to perfection or suggest you the right way to cook and eat it. 

Always been a good experience. 

Regular patron - the photos are taken from multiple occasions — we’ve probably eaten an entire cow by now 🐄
Food is of good quality esp if you like beef. For lunch, if you start after 1pm, be prepared to have a quick meal. They will prompt you to leave by all means before 2:30pm.

Came here just for this exquisite bowl of happiness and orgasm in the mouth. If you’re coming in group or pairs, would suggest you to book earlier. Or else, you will have a time restriction. The uni and beef was sooo good! And heavenly. Definitely worth eating if you’re a big big fan of beef and uni
Great quality and variation of food, follows Japanese tradition, pleasant service and not over priced (especially the lunch cost)
